                            <comment id="13765964" author="knoguchi" created="Thu, 12 Sep 2013 23:35:52 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Reason it gets lost is, we store C using PigStorage but ReadScalars tries to read it by a hardcoded InterStorage. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;...
[First mapreduce job]
Reduce Plan
C: Store(/.../deleteme6_C:PigStorage(&apos;,&apos;)) - scope-17
|
...

[Second mapreduce job]
    |   POUserFunc(org.apache.pig.impl.builtin.ReadScalars)[long] - scope-31
    |   |
    |   |---Constant(0) - scope-29
    |   |
    |   |---Constant(/.../deleteme6_C) - scope-30
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Trying to understand what the fix should be.&lt;br/&gt;
1. Make ReadScalars use the corresponding Loader.&lt;br/&gt;
2. Split relation &apos;C&apos; so that we store them in both PigStorage AND InterStorage.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m guessing latter, but appreciate your feedback.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13766790" author="mwagner" created="Fri, 13 Sep 2013 19:46:20 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d be in favor of 2 as well. There&apos;s no guarantee that the StoreFunc will also be a LoadFunc and the scalar will be a small file so writing an extra copy isn&apos;t costly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13768708" author="daijy" created="Mon, 16 Sep 2013 21:21:44 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;#2 has a simpler implementation as well. Just add one more check in ScalarVisitor.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13768718" author="knoguchi" created="Mon, 16 Sep 2013 21:30:25 +0100"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;#2 has a simpler implementation as well. Just add one more check in ScalarVisitor.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Yes, uploading a patch shortly.  Thanks Mark, Daniel.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13768748" author="knoguchi" created="Mon, 16 Sep 2013 21:57:47 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Uploading a patch that would make sure that ScalarVisitor is using the storefunc that is &lt;br/&gt;
(a) tmpStore &lt;br/&gt;
and&lt;br/&gt;
(b) using InterStorage&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Not sure if both checks are needed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Test case to follow.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13775557" author="knoguchi" created="Mon, 23 Sep 2013 19:49:15 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry for the delay.  Adding a test case.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13776795" author="daijy" created="Tue, 24 Sep 2013 22:45:20 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;+1. Please commit to trunk and 0.12 branch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13777868" author="knoguchi" created="Wed, 25 Sep 2013 19:27:50 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch committed to branch-0.12 and trunk.  &lt;br/&gt;
Thanks Mark and Daniel for your feedback!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
